news.title: Kolkata civic body to upload all information about buildings on portal
news.para: The municipal commissioner, Dhaval Jain, has asked the buildings department officials to prepare a ward-wise list of unauthorized buildings and upload the same on the KMC website for the benefit of potential flat-buyers.

news.title: Bihar REAT hindered by lack of quorum, raises concerns over 'illegal' appointments
news.para: The tribunal, however, could not pass an order as it lacked quorum. This was the second such case in the past one week when the tribunal could not pass an order for the same reason.

news.title: WeWork founder wants bankruptcy court's help in bid to repurchase company
news.para: Adam Neumann's new real estate company, Flow Global, has sought to buy WeWork out of bankruptcy, recently offering over $500 million.

news.title: NBCC bags new work orders worth Rs 23,500 crore in FY24
news.para: The company "has secured record new works of Rs 23,500 crore on consolidated basis and Rs 18,400 crore on standalone basis, as compared to Rs 6,700 crore (consolidated basis) and Rs 4,225 crore (standalone basis) in preceding fiscal."

news.title: Puravankara to redevelop project in Mumbai
news.para: The project has a cumulative estimated development potential of 4.10 lakh sq ft carpet area, with over 2.15 lakh sq ft available for sale, and a potential gross development value (GDV) of over Rs 2,000 crore.

news.title: UK: Taylor Wimpey reaffirms 2024 outlook as sales rate inches higher
news.para: The British housing market has seen green shoots of stability at the start of 2024 on easing mortgage rates after battling subdued demand for most of last year, but the delay in central bank's monetary policy loosening and incessant macro-economic woes have tempered hopes of a better-paced recovery.

news.title: UP-RERA imposes penalty upon an allottee for misuse of process of law
news.para: Uttar Pradesh RERA took strong objection to the fourth complaint by this allottee and imposed a cost of Rs 5,000 upon him.

news.title: Real estate sales to grow 8-10% in FY25: Ind-Ra
news.para: The residential sales registered 25% growth year-on-year for the top eight cities in in 9M FY24, despite price increases and sticky interest-rates, according to India Ratings and Research.

news.title: Awfis Space Solutions get Sebi's nod to float IPO
news.para: Awfis Space Solutions' proposed IPO is a combination of fresh issue equity shares worth Rs 160 crore and an OFS component of over 1 crore equity shares, as per the draft papers.

news.title: DVAC probes alleged PMAY fund misuse in Trichy’s Marudhur village
news.para: Inspector G Sakthivel filed a case on April 12 against 10 officials of the panchayat raj and rural development department.

news.title: Ludhiana civic body cracks whip on illegal constructions
news.para: An illegal under construction colony on Jassian road and an encroachment on road portion in Tagore Nagar were also demolished.

news.title: NCLT admits Indiabulls Housing's insolvency plea against Subhash Chandra
news.para: ​A two-member Delhi bench of the NCLT directed initiation of personal insolvency proceedings against Zee Entertainment Enterprises Ltd (ZEEL) Chairman Emeritus Chandra, who was a guarantor for a loan given to Essel group firm Vivek Infracon Ltd.

news.title: K Raheja Corp to redevelop SOBO Central Mall into luxury residences
news.para: Spread over 1.3 acres in prime Haji Ali locality, the mall is expected to make way for an around 50-storey sea-view superstructure with nearly 250,000 sq ft development potential.

news.title: Accacia raises $6.5 million in pre-series A round led by Illuminate Financial
news.para: "We have already deployed our solution to over 25 million sq ft of real estate," said Annu Talreja, founder and CEO of Accacia.

news.title: US-based Quanex to buy UK's Tyman for $976 million
news.para: The acquisition comes at a time U.S. housebuilders are cutting prices and offering other incentives to increase sales amid hurdles created for many first time buyers by higher mortgage rates.

news.title: Kesoram Industries' net loss widens to Rs 244.42 crore in Q4 FY24
news.para: Kesoram Industries' total consolidated income stood at Rs 1,093.96 crore in Q4 FY24, a growth of from Rs 1,070.82 crore it recorded in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: Asking prices for homes in UK rise by 1.7% in April: Rightmove
news.para: Property website Rightmove said on Monday its asking prices for residential properties rose by 1.7% in the four weeks to April 13 when compared with the same period last year.
